{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_hine_ver02/data/sn82016181/00529046066/1929112301/0484.xml":{"full_text":"TIMOTHY TINKER\nHe WORT PUWIT\nyou, MISTEH,\n-ws JUST\nPUFUL\nSAY!\nVO HKTf. TO MEET\nHIM OURING\nBUSINESS HOURS\nK THEM\u2022 y\nBy Tom Culver well\nWhite House\nPresident Hoover will wear a\nblack crepe sieeve band for 30 days\nas a mark of mourning for the late\nSecretary Good.\nA White House proclamation re\nminded all citizens of their duty to\nfurnish full information to census\ntakers who will start counting noses\nnest April.\nA 35 pound live turkey, gift of a\nStockton, Calif., poultry ranch, ar\nrived at the White House for the\npremdential Thanksgiving feast\nPresident Hoover canceled many\nengagements to devote time to com\nelating his messabe to Congress.\nSenate\nThe Senate adjourned until the\nregular session beginning Dec. 2.\nMany Senators hurried away to their\nhomes during the recess.\nHouse\nThe House followed the Senate\u2019s\naction in adjourning its special ses\nsion.\nRep W. W. Grist, 71, nt Pennayl\nvania, was critically ill at Mt.\nClemen., Mich.\nPower\nThe Federal Power Commission\nappealed to the War, Interior and\nAgriculture Departments to aid in\ndisposing of Ave yearn accumulated\naccountng work.\nArmy\nArmy orders revealed that Presi\ndent Hoover contemplates erection\nof a War Department building to\nhouse all military activities here\nunder one roof.\nFire\nFire doomed an orphan asylum at\nTroy, N. Y., but the IMO children\nwere led to safety without any being\nbiju red.\nOn a front veral hundred miles\nlong, a disastrous forest Are raged\nin northern California, menacing\nseveral towns ami wiping out the\nvillage of Montura.\nFOOD\nSHOW\nCLOSES\nTONIGHT\nAll Grand !\u2018riu\nWinnert Will He\nAnnounced\nHe Sure to Ite Present\nY ou May Take Your Gift\nor Prize Home\nWashington Auditorium\nCrime\nDistrict police held a prominent\nClearwater, Fla., merchant on\ncharges of embezzling |1000 from a\nG-st store where he was formerly\nassistant manager.\nA colored banlit was hurried in\nhis escape after taking $4000 from\na Pittsburgh bank and dropped bills\nI of all denominations in flight.\nScience\nA \u201clie detector\u201d machine was to\nbe demonstrated at a murder care in\nSeattle, Wash.\nJustice\nHarry K, Sligh was convicted at\nOcilla, Ga., of slaying Harry Loving\ni to collect $50,000 insurance and sen\ntenced to life imprisonment.\nLabor\nA jury was completed inthe sec\nond trial of Alfred Hoffman, union\norganizer, and three strikers for\nrioting and resisting officers in\n[labor disorders at Marion, N. C.\nTragedy\nA World War veteran being treat\ned for nervous disorder at a Trenton,\nN. J., sanitarium, was held at the\nstate insane hospital after he fatally\nshot an attendant.\nA Buffalo pastor hung himself in\nbin garage. No reason for his\nsuicide was given.\nDisaster\nStories of heroism and sacrifice\ndrifted in as relief work started\nalong the devastated shore of Burin\nPeninsula. Revised death lists show\nthat 28 perished in the tidal wave\nthat swept the coast.\nPestilence claimed 400 lives within\nthe week at St. Christopher, British\nWest Indies, according to reports at\nSan Juan, Porto Rico.\nEducation\nJohn D. Rockefeller Jr. gave\nChicago U. between 11,000,000 and\n12,000,000 for a foreign students\u2019\ni clubhouse, bringing Rockefeller gifts\nto the institution to more than\n$46,000,000.\nN. Y. Stock Market\nis Closed Today\nI\nBrokerage Houses Work to\nClear Up Work; Full Time\nSessions Will Be Resumed\nBy United Press\nNEW YORK.-The Stock Ex\nchange and other financial markets\nwere closed today as brokerage\nhouses worked feverishly to catch\nup with their books after the recent\nrush of business.\nTrading for the week was con\nsidered normal, which is believed to\nhave been the moving factor in the\naction of exchange in ordering full\nsessions for the first three days of\nnext week.\nThe exchange will also be closed\nThursday, Eriday and Saturday of\nThanksgiving week but the member\noffices were to be open to clear up\ntrades.\nThe committee on arrangements\nasked the member houses to give\nemployes a holiday Thanksgiving.\nJOHN D. ROCKEFELLER JR.\nGives Chicago U. a million\n(See under \"Education\u201d)\nChina\nPresident Chiang Kai-shek said al\nHankow on his return from the front\nthat China\u2019s civil war was ended.\nFrance\nFormer Premier Clemenceau's\ndeath was expected momentarily al\nParis.\nGreat Britain\nHenry Ford\u2019s decision to raise\nwages to aid business depression\nwas heartily received in British la\nbor circles, according to London ob\nservers.\nPalestine\nArabs of Palestine, Trans-Jordan\u2014\nia and Syria notified Jerusalen\nauthorities that they would resort to\nforce unless Jews discontinued wor\nshiping at the Wailing Wall.\nRussia\nA general offensive by 20,000\nSoviet troops began along the wes\ntern frontier of China with Man\nchili as the immediate objective.\nLeague of Nations\nThe mandates commission of the\nLeague of Nations at Geneva re\nfused Britain\u2019s request for a special\ngroup to survey the Palestine situa\ntion.\nMystery\nA memorial service will be held a'\nCopenhagen Dec. 14 for the 70 Dan\nish cadets on the training ship\nKobenhavn which was never hear\nfrom after leaving Montevideo sev\neeral months ago.\nComedy\nAn aged visitor here from Exeter\nN. H., pulled a lever on a red bo:\nbut no slot opened to receive a let\nter he wanted to mail. Firemen re\nspending to the alarm thus turner\nki, mailed it for him.\nNames\nThe Prince of Wales showed hi:\nskill as a pilot by making a sob\nflight at London in extremely\n\u201cbumpy\u201d weather.\nPresident Vasquez of Santo Do\nmingo will be operated on next wee!\nat Johns Hopkins Hospital.\nReligion\nDetermined not to profit from the\nincreased attendance, the trustees of\nthe little Quaker Church where\nPresident Hoover worships voted to\nabolish the customary Sunday offer\ning.\nCardinal O\u2019Connell closed the Mal\nden, Mass., cemetery pending inves\ntigation of reported cures among\nthousands of pilgrims who flocked to\nthe grave of the young priest.\nCivic Affairs\nAsst. Police Chief Shelby\u2019s coun\nsel demanded a public trial of the\nCommissioners to clear him of\ncharges brought by the first Mc\nPherson grand jury.\nDr. George H. Richardson was re\nelected president of the Federation\nof Civic Associations.\nWeather\nWashington awoke to find the first\nsnow of the winter blanketing the\ncity.\nMiscellany\nA Chicago tax assessor was in\ndicted for not paying his own taxes\namounting to $43,000.\nSports\nHarry Sinclair\u2019s first official act\nafter leaving the District Jail was\nto appoint John Lowe to succeed th\u00a9\nlate Sam Hildreth as chief trainer\nof his Rancocas racing stable at\nJobstown, N. J.\nThe Yale-Harvard tradition-clad\ngrid battle headlined the eastern\nfootball schedule.\nAviation\nOne of New York\u2019s flying cop\u00a9\ntried to stop his plane by grabbing\nthe tail after it had run over him.\nHe took an impromptu ride, dropped\nuninjured as the plane crashed.\nBaron Von Warthausen, his small\nplane \u201cKamerad\u201d and his Siamese\ncat and homed toad mascots arrived\nat Berlin, completing a globe-trot\nting tour of some 15 months.\nAmelia Earhart set a new world\nspeed flying record for women of\n184.17 miles per hour at Los Angeles\nAccidents\nWhen two Dallas, Tex., trolley\ncars crashed head-on, 27 passengers\niwere injured.\nWhen Superlatives\nGet Together\nWith the advance of advertising, the use of\nsuperlatives is rare, and growing rarer. But\nwhat a jumble and confusion they make when\nthey do get together!\nIt was not many years ago when advertis\ning was judged by which piece of copy made\nthe \"loudest\u201d noise.\" A good advertisement\nin those days was a \u201cscreamer.\"\nThese words and phrases are now becoming\nas ineffective as they are unpopular;\n\"GREATEST\u201d \"LARGEST\"\n\u201cBEST\u201d \u201cBIGGEST\u201d\n\"FINEST\" \u201cMOST AMAZING\u201d\n\"STUPENDOUS\u201d \u201cWITHOUT PARALLEL\u201d\nThat advertising today produces best, which\ntells a simple, attractive, truthful story. The\npublic is more interested in the merchandise\nitself, than in noisy phrases concerning it.\nPerhaps the chief reason for the compelling,\naccurate character of today\u2019s advertising is\nthe practical abandonment of the so-called\n\"ballyhoo,\u201d circus-type, superlative appeaL\nWhen superlatives get together, there is\nconfusion\u2014but, fortunately for advertising,\nthey seldom do.\nRead Advertising For Its Truth\u2019s Sake!\nBefore You Invest\u2014Investigate!\nThe appearance of this notice in\nthese columns is evidence that this\nnewspaper supports and co-operates\nwith the Better Business Bureau of\nWashington.\nThe Better Business\nBureau\nof Washington\n336 Evening Star Building\nTelephone National 8164","height":"21732","width":"14496"}}
